spanGrp.span: sinpa chara akheh ruwng sinnu̠ chara akheh ṭhocha jenu̠
had a boy and a girl
vachara hin to unsah lopā jenu̠
Her children loved her very much
atarāng ki vapāl cha je te
achim ma vanu̠ hinto thọcha ve
hangthi oh dahtung kāma doh vati mo e
"Wake upǃ How did you leave me? How?" she said and cried and cried.
How?" she said and cried and cried.
vachalanu̠ to ahe le doh chechenu̠ vaṭa-vaṭa-vaṭa-vaṭa nāte
The daughter kept on coming and crying
dah lapu̠nu̠ nangte ṭhocha mo kada te dali ivangle vati mo eh
"Why, old woman, I thought you've already died. Why are you coming back?"
vachalnu̠ ku̠ng dāli avang ṭhu̠ mo eh?
(Asking) his sisterː "Why did you come with her back?"
vahmi khol thung tingnāl eh din chee choo nu̠
There are lots of earthworms inside her eyeholes.
vāna khol thung tingnāl eh kira sọ chee chou nu̠, din chee choo nu̠
Inside her ears there worms leaking out, lots of them.
dah lapunu̠ peedal sọ-sọ dahli avang th- ṭhu̠ mo eh?
This old woman is so dirty, why did you come alone with her?
kanu̠ nanu̠ unsah lonu̠ kāvang ṭhu̠ ve
Since I love my... our mother, I came back with her.
vājal vāso dinu̠ kāvang ṭhu̠ cha va ve
I came back with her because she resurrected.
"Wake up and changeǃ", said. "The Gmelina tree has changedǃ"
her son (said) "The Gmelina tree has changed"
As (she) was saying "Wake up and change"
(he) was saying "The Gmelina tree has changed."
pavung ahlija vada ṭol ja nāte
vangle nu̠ ṭhān thung ha hlu nu̠ thọ cha
went back to the grave and died
After that she never returned again.
vachapa tuwng kheh ing adal ahlija danite,
mi iṭhọ hin he ajal jeso
vakowng hrin peṭe so ivang jal hlo-hlo hrang varende,
might newly change the skin and resurrect,
the son said: the Gmelina tree has changed.
pavung thing heeng atung heeng vahang val thung
Now, when the Gmelina tree grows up,
vakowng he thabol nu̠ ikāng-ikāng pho-pho akāng pho-pho akāng pho-pho nu̠
the bark of the tree becomes thick and burns with a cracking sound
it dries up and ehm that
palu̠ to ajung ṭal pow nu̠ ināl ring rung
the old bark falls down and becomes smooth
kum sowru̠ khu̠so danite vakowng to ṭumkheh
If it is too old enough, the cover again
akang pho-pho akang pho nu̠ ṭal pow khu̠nu̠
changes and decends to the ground and
vanu̠ tuwng adal ahlija vada thung tuwng
when his mother said "Wake up and changeǃ"
anihin he iṭhọ ine am maso, ahli hlo-hlo idal ine am maso
there will be no dead and we will never get old
ahli hlo-hlo hin sin sung pāl va hin sin de
we would change and live on.
vachapa tuwng amato da ma nu̠ pavung ahlija vadate
But the son didn't say that and say gmelina
thing tata vapha isow ahli hlo-hlo ahli hlo hlo nu̠
after a long time, it peeled off
it changed into new again and again
ata tuwng ethọ ehring he tuwng eam vahin sin
likewise, we have dead and live among us
napi napu̠ hin tuwng dapā nu̠ mah
